This committee advises the Assistant Vice Chancellor of Campus Planning and Community Resources on issues of campus Transportation and Parking Services transportation and parking.

Membership includes the following (taken from the UC Davis AAC website): 2 Academic Senate, 1 Academic Federation, 2 Staff, 2 Graduate Students, 2 Undergraduate Students, 1 Visitor Representative (Chair of SEMG), 1 Representative for the Disabled Community (Member of DIAAC), 2 AtLarge Members (Members are selected from the pool of TPAAC applicants), 5 Ex Officio, NonVoting members: Chair, Director of Transportation and Parking Services; Representative, Police; Representative, Design and Construction Management; Representative, Unitrans; Representative, Administrative and Resource Management.

Meetings are held on the second Thursday of each month.
